com.github.gwtd3.api.arrays

Class ArrayList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.gwtd3.api.arrays.ArrayList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>, RandomAccess

    public class ArrayList<E>
extends Object
implements List<E>, RandomAccess, Cloneable, Serializable
    A List wrapping a Javascript Array.

    The backed array should contains the type of object specified by <E> or ClassCastException may be raised.

    Also this list cannot be used to wrap arrays of primitive wrapper (Boolean, Double, etc...).

    TODO: fix the issue above by creating a specialized class a List with a specific accessor.
